///**
// * A {@link QueryCompiler} implementation that compiles Java source to bytecode in memory (no filesystem output).
// * <p>
// * Like the filesystem-backed {@link QueryCompilerImpl}, this implementation uses {@code java.class.path} plus an
// * optional extra class directory for resolving compilation dependencies (e.g., Groovy-generated bytecode). The key
// * difference is that compiled classes are defined directly into a classloader rather than written to disk.
// * <p>
// * <h2>Key invariants</h2>
// * <ul>
// * <li>No formula compiled by this compiler ever depends on another formula compiled by this or any other
// * QueryCompiler.</li>
// * <li>The classloader is created as a child of the provided parent classloader.</li>
// * <li>Groovy/dynamic classes must be written to the extra class directory before formulas referencing them are
// * compiled.</li>
// * </ul>
// */
// public class InMemoryQueryCompiler implements QueryCompiler {
